groups.name: First Production

extra_copy.content:
• Premium seating and cabin materials throughout, including open-pore wood décor
  • Custom driver profiles enabled by 12-way, power adjustable front seats, steering column and side mirrors
  • Premium audio system with more power, tweeters, surround speakers and subwoofer for an enhanced listening experience
  • Tinted glass roof with ultraviolet and infrared protection
  • Auto dimming, power folding, heated side mirrors
  • LED fog lamps
  • Rear heated seats with their own USB ports
  • Center console with covered storage and docking for two smartphones

groups.description:
Safety

Model 3 is designed to achieve 5-star safety ratings in every category.
  • Eight airbags for driver and passengers
  • Side Collision Warning & Automatic Emergency Braking
  • Electronic stability and traction control
  • Full LED lighting

Convenience

  • Keyless entry and remote climate control using the Tesla app
  • 15″ touchscreen with onboard maps & navigation
  • Wi-Fi and LTE internet connectivity
  • Voice activated controls
  • Back-up camera
  • 60/40 split folding rear seats

Warranty

  • Vehicle: 4 year, 50,000 mile limited warranty
  • Battery: 8 year, 100,000 mile (120,000 mile with Long Range Battery)

extra_copy.content:
Autopilot is an increasingly capable suite of safety and convenience features that make personal transportation safer and more enjoyable.

Safety is Standard

  • Automatic Emergency Braking

    Detects objects that the car may impact and applies the brakes accordingly

  • Side Collision Warning

    Warns the driver of potential collisions with obstacles alongside the car

  • Front Collision Warning

    Warns of impending collisions with slower moving or stationary cars

• 15” touchscreen display
  • Dual zone climate control system
  • FM/Internet streaming radio
  • Textile seating
  • Center console with open storage and two USB ports
The first Model 3 configuration to enter production features a long range battery, rear wheel drive and premium upgrades throughout.
Additional configurations, including the entry level Model 3 without upgrades, will become available as production ramps.

$APF2.name: Full Self-Driving Capability

extra_copy.content: Model 3 will pilot itself along freeways and automatically park at your destination.

$APF2.description:
In the future, Model 3 will be capable of conducting trips with no action required by the person in the driver's seat.

This feature is dependent upon extensive software validation and regulatory approval, which may vary by jurisdiction.

$APPB.name: Enhanced Autopilot

extra_copy.content: In the future, tell Model 3 where to go and it will navigate with no driver intervention.

$APPB.description:
Model 3 will match speed to traffic conditions, keep within a lane, automatically change lanes, transition from one freeway to another, exit the freeway and self-park at your destination.

Features are rolling out over time via over-the-air software updates.

$BT37.name: Long Range Battery

extra_copy.content:
5.6 sec 0-60 mph
750 miles free annual Supercharging

$BT37.description:
The first Model 3 configuration to enter production will feature our largest battery.

  • 310 mile range
  • 0 to 60 mph in 5.1 seconds
  • 135 mph top speed
  • Half a charge in 20 minutes using Tesla's global Supercharger network

$MDL3.name: Model 3
$MDL3.description: Deliveries are beginning in the US based on whether you own a Tesla and when you placed your reservation, and will continue by country.

$PRM31.name: Premium Upgrades

extra_copy.content: Our premium package adds upgraded features throughout Model 3

$PRM31.description:
Elevate your interior experience with upgraded features and premium materials.

  • Tinted glass roof with ultraviolet and infrared protection
  • Enhanced audio system with more power, surround speakers and subwoofer
  • Premium black seating materials with seat heaters throughout
